    "narrative": "The Austin Waves\u2019 lineup today is headlined by **Gunnar Henderson**, who earns a standout 83.29 score against Bello. His elite rating is driven by a massive +16% park factor and a favorable platoon advantage that vaults him into must-start territory as our primary engine for R and HR. **Kyle Tucker** (73.60) also presents a high-floor profile, benefiting from a solid 0.372 xwOBA against Taillon, while **Drake Baldwin** (70.03) serves as our most efficient catching option, capitalizing on a weak matchup against Painter (5.25 xERA) and a high-leverage spot in the #2 hole. **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (69.24) remains a core pillar; despite a slight platoon dip, his overall profile and cleanup-adjacent spot in the lineup ensure he remains a premier run-producing asset.\n\nWe are paying close attention to **Nasim Nunez** (62.48), whose score is propped up by his aggressive base-running profile. Given our mandate to prioritize SB, **Nasim Nunez** remains active despite the lower end of the batting order, as his ability to manufacture speed-based value outweighs the marginal output of bench options. The most difficult decision today involved **Nolan Schanuel** (56.02), who missed the cut by the narrowest of margins. While **Nolan Schanuel** provided a stable floor, the optimizer favored **Coby Mayo** (56.63) due to a superior park factor, which ultimately provided the edge required to clear the starting threshold.\n\nWe have exercised caution with **Marcell Ozuna**, who is benched today with a score of 43.46. Facing a high-caliber arm like Woodruff (2.90 xERA), the risk of a zero-production day outweighs the limited upside, leading us to favor higher-efficiency matchups across the board. While the weather looks clear, we are monitoring the lineup for **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.**, as his significant platoon disadvantage against a lefty (Hudson, B) makes him a candidate for mid-game substitution should his efficiency crater early. Overall, the squad is positioned to maximize R and SB, assuming **Gunnar Henderson** and **Kyle Tucker** can navigate their respective matchups effectively.",
